## 2026-03-29 - Batch token mutation routes have no partial-failure rollback
- Added three atomic batch methods to TokenStore: `batchUpdateTokens`, `batchRenameTokens`, `batchMoveTokens`
- Each method validates all inputs upfront, snapshots affected sets, applies all in-memory changes, saves once, and rolls back everything on any error
- Updated route handlers in `tokens.ts` to call the new batch methods instead of looping over individual `updateToken`/`renameToken`/`moveToken` calls

